  "title": "Meters in a simple circuit",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a rectangular circuit diagram with one battery and one resistor. There is a branch connected in parallel with the resistor. That branch is labeled 2. Below R, there is a branch labeled 1.\" height=\"151\" src=\"/images/1b3002f0c8342bf2d6554bf23140522b.png\" width=\"150\"></div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A student connects a resistor of unknown resistance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to a battery of unknown voltage. The student connects a voltmeter and ammeter in the circuit to measure the current and voltage in order to determine the power <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>P</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> dissipated by the resistor. Which of the following correctly describes the ammeter or voltmeter and how it must be connected in the circuit to make accurate measurements?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The voltmeter must have a resistance much less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and be placed at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The ammeter must have a resistance much less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and be placed at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The voltmeter must have a resistance much less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and be placed at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The ammeter must have a resistance much less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and be placed at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
